  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Envelope 1: Integrated Shelter and WASH assistance to improve dignified living in Idleb</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Syria remains a complex humanitarian crisis compounded by over ten years of hostilities, protracted displacements and prolonged consequences including destruction of civilian infrastructure. In NWS armed hostilities, airstrikes and shelling continues to persist daily. As of January 2022, close to 1.7 million people are living across 1,401 IDP sites in NWS. IDP sites are overcrowded and 86% of IDPs are living in critical density situations. Overcrowding, lack of privacy and forced to share shelters with non-family members increases risks for women and girls. (source HNO 2022) 
 
For over ten years, humanitarian programming has predominantly focused on emergency life-saving responses, however, given the protracted crisis, the humanitarian context has evolved and there is need for humanitarian response to focus more on dignified living conditions. 
 
The proposed project provides life-saving integrated assistance and will enhance dignified living and resilience of IDPs in camps in Harim and Ariha districts of Idleb governorate. SI will provide under envelope 1 dignified shelters and integrated WASH support to a total of 2,180 individuals in IDP camps with high-needs (100% IDPs). 
 
SI proposes to provide and install 280 dignified shelters for IDPs in Al Faraj-Al Ghab, Al Sinaah and Al Salam camps. In addition, SI will distribute hygiene kits and conduct hygiene promotion sessions for all camp residents in Al Faraj-Al Ghab, improve their water and sewage system, as well as provide solid waste management support (total target beneficiaries: 2,845 individuals).</narrative>
  </description>
